observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management, through:

The GSO fast-tracks the preparation for the one-time cleansing of the PPE accounts so that an actual physical count can finally be conducted; 
The Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory count on all the properties of the Municipality, including the Lands, Land Improvements, Buildings, and Constructions-in-Progress; 

The Inventory Committee and Accounting Office reconcile the results of the count with the property and accounting records; and

The Property Officer ensures that property cards are maintained for all the properties of the LGU.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:

Individually evaluate the existence and validity of aged claims and affect the reversion of claims to the Government Equity account, if warranted; 

Submit the Journal Entry Voucher/s for adjustments made in the books, together with the result of the evaluation indicating, as remarks, the reason/s for reversion of each aged account.

We recommended the following courses of action:
The Municipal Accountant:
Adopt the perpetual inventory system and record the purchase of supplies first as inventory and not directly as Construction-in-Progress;
Establish and maintain the required Supply Ledger Cards for each supply inventory to be regularly reconciled with the GSO records;
Make an adjusting entry to recognize the construction materials inventory and reduce the recorded CIP;
The Municipal General Services Officer:
Establish and maintain the required stock cards per inventory item to be regularly reconciled with the accounting office SLCs;
Prepare a summary of requisition of materials with particulars as to quantity and for which specific project these requisitions are for, to be submitted to the accounting office as a basis for recording as CIP or expense; and
The Municipal Engineer:
Specify in their requisition slip to the GSO the exact quantity of materials requested, and the specific project for which it will be utilized, for proper recording and costing of PPEs.

We recommended that:
The Management fast-tracks the implementation of the one-time cleansing of the PPE accounts to present a more reliable financial statement;
The Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory count on all the properties of the Municipality, including the Lands, Land Improvements, Buildings, and Constructions-in-Progress;
The Inventory Committee and Accounting Office reconcile the results of the count with the property and accounting records; and
The Management ensures that the Property Officer maintains property cards and all the properties of the LGU.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive, as the Chairperson, together with other co-chairpersons and members of the Local School Board:
Ensure that the SEF budget is approved on or before October 31 of the current year, to give more time for the provincial LSBs to consider augmentation to municipalities;
Ensure that the approved SEF budget is furnished to concerned offices in compliance with Item 6.1 of the DEPED-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 1, s. 2017; and strictly comply with other deadlines outlined in the said guidelines.

We recommended that the Management through:
the GSO fast tracks the preparation for the one-time cleansing of the PPE accounts so that an actual physical count can finally be conducted;
the Inventory Committee to conduct inventory count on all the properties of the Municipality including the Lands, Land Improvements, Buildings, and Constructions-in-Progress;
the Inventory Committee and Accounting Office reconcile the results of the count with the property and accounting record; and
the Property Officer ensures that property cards are maintained for all the properties of the LGU.

We recommended that the Management, through the Municipal Accountant:
Individually evaluate the existence and validity of aged claims and affect the reversion of claims to the Government Equity account, if warranted;
Submit the Journal Entry Voucher/s for adjustments made in the books, together with the result of the evaluation indicating as remarks, the reason/s for reversion of each aged account.

